OL,6,FBy pleading guilty Cross has been told
OL,7,Fthere will be a reduction in his jail
OL,8,Fsentence. The prosecution followed an
OL,9,Finvestigation by North Wales Police.
OL,11,FAlison Storey, Specialist Prosecutor
OL,12,Fwith the CPS Special Crime Division,
OL,13,Fsaid: "Miles Cross preyed on four
OL,14,Fpeople in a distressed state and
OL,15,Fknowingly provided a substance
OL,16,Fintended to end their lives.
OL,18,F"His actions were purely for financial
OL,19,Fgain, and he made the process of
OL,20,Fordering the chemical online easy and
OL,21,Faccessible.
